The paper focuses on ranking on large-scale graphs, which is a fundamental problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SOC). The proposed paradigm shift for PageRank involves understanding why the ranking algorithm gives a particular ranking result, which is related to interpretability (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a family of effective and scalable algorithms, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
